cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on optimizing the performance of a cellular network with caches at every base station. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the caching policies proposed in the paper are fully distributed. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a methodology to assess the performance of interacting caches. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper proposes a novel analytical methodology. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security concerns related to caching in cellular networks.
